{
  "texts": [
    "One strategy to address basic questions like those above is to render them moot by exclusively using simple, transparent model classes (Lipton, 2018).",
    "Evidence exists that this \"interpretable-only\" strategy may be appropriate in some settings (Knight, 2017).",
    "However, even interpretable model classes can be grossly affected by training data issues (Huber, 1981; Cook et al., 1982; Cook & Weisberg, 1982).",
    "Moreover, as the performance penalty of interpretable models grows, their continued use becomes harder to justify.",
    "With the growing use of black-box models, we need better methods to analyze and understand black-box model decisions."
  ]
}